Floral micromorphological characteristics observed using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) have proven to be useful for taxonomic delimitation and phylogenetic inference of various groups, including Adoxaceae (
 Konarska, 2017), Crassulaceae (
 Giuliani et al., 2018), Nymphaeaceae (
 Coiro and Barone Lumaga, 2018), Lentibulariaceae (
 Płachno et al., 2019), and Rosaceae (
 Song et al., 2020). Notably, taxonomic and systematic relevance of floral micromorphology, including that of the corolla, calyx, style, and stigma, has been confirmed within Boraginaceae (
 Bigazzi et al., 1999; 
 Bacchetta et al., 2000; 
 Bigazzi and Selvi, 2000; 
 Akçin, 2009).
